The other factor is legal. The U.S. Federal Trade Commission (and others) have been investigating Instagram for suspected violations of the Privacy Act of 1974. By downloading your data, Instagram could potentially be violating that law.
Right now there’s no indication that Instagram will be taking any action against anyone who downloads all their data. But if you’re a parent who used Instagram to monitor your kid’s school activities, you may want to consider deleting all your data from its servers, just in case Facebook decides to change its data sharing policies.
